  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My friend block a person on what's app how could I know really he is blocked?",
  "response": "If your friend has blocked someone on WhatsApp, there are a few ways you might be able to tell if the block is real, but remember, it's important to respect privacy and not to intrude too much into others' personal matters. Here are some signs that could indicate someone has been blocked on WhatsApp:\n\n1. **Profile Picture and Status**: If the person your friend blocked can no longer see your friend's profile picture or status updates, this could be a sign of being blocked. However, this is not definitive as some people might choose to hide their profile picture and status from everyone or non-contacts.\n\n2. **Last Seen and Online Status**: If your friend has their last seen or online status visible to everyone or their contacts, and the blocked person can no longer see this information, it might indicate a block. Again, this isn't foolproof as settings can be adjusted to limit this visibility.\n\n3. **Messages**: If the blocked person tries to send a message to your friend, they will still be able to do so, but the message will only show one check mark (indicating it was sent) and will never show a second check mark (indicating it was delivered). However, this could also mean that your friend is simply offline or has connectivity issues.\n\n4. **Calls**: If the blocked person attempts to call your friend on WhatsApp, the call will not go through. Instead, it will seem as if it's ringing but won't connect. Again, this could also be due to other technical issues.\n\n5. **Group Chats**: The blocked person can still see your friend in group chats, but they won't be able to see when your friend is online or their last seen. Your friend will also not be able to see the blocked person's updates in the group.\n\n6. **Direct Confirmation**: The most direct way to know if someone is blocked is if your friend tells you they have blocked this person. However, it's important to respect their privacy and not pressure them into sharing such details if they are uncomfortable.\n\nRemember, these signs are not definitive as they can be influenced by other factors like privacy settings or technical issues. The best way to know for sure is through direct communication with your friend, but again, respect their privacy and boundaries.",
